Never use em dashes, semicolons, or colons in any prose drafted for Nick. Applies to cover letters, emails, applications, recruiter notes, LinkedIn copy, any prose-shaped writing. Replace with periods (split into two sentences), commas, or a restructure that doesn't need any of the three.

**Why:** Nick's settled writing-style rule. The no-em-dash half is already in [[PRINCIPAL_IDENTITY.md]]. The no-semicolon half was added 2026-06-11 during the PM cover-letter drafting (Tennis Australia, Prezzee, The Onset). The no-colon extension was confirmed 2026-06-13 when Nick approved swapping colons out of The Onset letter the same way as semicolons. The pattern is that Nick reads these punctuation marks as visually similar and they break the conversational rhythm he wants.

**How to apply:** Before delivering any prose written for Nick, scan for the em dash, semicolon, and colon characters. If present, fix them. Don't ask permission, this is a settled style rule. Hyphens inside compound words (e.g. "grassroots-to-Grand-Slam", "fit-for-purpose") are fine. Parentheses are fine. Periods and commas do most of the work. Email subject lines should use a hyphen or pipe instead of an em dash.

Related: [[feedback-nick-stakeholder-email-style]], [[feedback-status-updates-must-persist-to-project-files]].
